data.text:
Manisha Koirala is a film actress and social worker. She was born on 16 August 1970 in Kathmandu, Nepal. She grew up in New Delhi and completed her schooling from VKM School, Varanasi, and Army Public School, Dhaula Kuan, Delhi. She earned a diploma in Film Making from New York University.

Her father, Prakash Koirala is a former politician from Nepal. Her mother, Sushma Koirala is a homemaker. She has a brother, Sidhharth Koirala.

Manisha Koirala’s favourites

Her hobbies include reading and travelling.

Her favourite films are, Masoom, Kagaz Ke Phool, One Flew Over The Cuckoo’s Nest, An Officer, and A Gentleman.

Her favourite film director is Mani Ratnam.

Her favourite actors are Kamal Haasan, Ingrid Bergman, Meryl Streep, and Whoopi Goldberg.

Her favourite books are ‘The Idiot’ by Fyodor Dostoyevsky, ‘The World According to Garp’ by John Irwing, and ‘Fear of Fifty’ by Erica Jong.

Her favourite Ghazal singers are Begum Akhtar and Mehdi Hasan.

Her favourite travelling destinations are Kashmir and London.

Interesting facts about Manisha Koirala

Manisha Koirala is the granddaughter of former Nepali Prime Minister Bishweshwar Prasad Koirala.

She is a trained Bharatnatyam and Manipuri dancer.

In her teenage years, Manisha dreamed of becoming a doctor, however, after doing a few modelling assignments, she decided to pursue a career in acting.

Manisha Koirala’s debut

Manisha Koirala made her acting debut with the 1989 Nepali film ‘Feri Bathola.’

She appeared in her first Bollywood film ‘Saudagar’ in the year 1991.

Apart from working in Hindi films, she has also worked in Nepali, Tamil, Telugu and Malayalam film industries.

She worked with her brother, Sidhharth Koirala, in the film ‘Anwar.’

In the 1990s, she was counted among India’s most beautiful actresses.

Manisha Koirala’s marriage

Manisha Koirala had a huge crush on the actor, Sanjay Dutt in her early years in the entertainment industry.

She married Samrat Dahal, a businessman from Nepal, in the year 2010. The couple took a divorce in 2012.

Awards

She has been honoured with Filmfare Critics Awards for her roles in films, Akele Hum Akele Tum (1995), Khamoshi: The Musical (1996), Dil Se… (1998), Lajja (2001), and Company (2002).

Manisha Koirala’s 1998 film ‘Dil Se…’ with Bollywood superstar, Shah Rukh Khan, is considered one of the best Bollywood films ever produced.

In the year 2012, Manisha Koirala was diagnosed with cancer. She received her treatment from America.

Manisha Koirala’s filmography

Manisha Koirala’s popular films are, Dil Se… (1998), Bombay (1995), 1942: A Love Story (1994), Agni Sakshi (1996), Kachche Dhaage (1999), Anmol (1993), Lajja (2001), Dear Maya (2017), Sanju (2018), and Lust Stories (2018).
